particularly managing people who are travelling from all parts of the world.

43
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:15,120
On top of this, China is accused of human rights abuses against the Wiga Muslims,

44
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:18,840
and there is controversy around the tennis player Peng Shui.

45
00:03:18,879 --> 00:03:21,879
But, despite the issues facing the games organisers,

46
00:03:21,879 --> 00:03:26,800
they want to put on an event that is hard to forget for good reasons.

47
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,719
Stephen used the word memorable.

48
00:03:29,719 --> 00:03:34,800
Well, seeing athletes hurtle down an icy track at 130 kilometres an hour

49
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:38,840
on what looks like a tea tray is certainly unforgettable.

50
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:42,039
This is what they call the skeleton.

51
00:03:42,039 --> 00:03:47,640
Hmm, let's hear more about the preparations for the games from the BBC's Stephen MacDonald.

52
00:03:49,319 --> 00:03:54,039
The games will be held in a freezing, mostly dry area.

53
00:03:54,039 --> 00:03:57,080
A mountain of snow-making is required.

54
00:03:57,080 --> 00:04:01,000
But this can make for quick, dynamic runs.

55
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:05,920
The athletes we spoke to said these sites will make for high quality competition.

56
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:10,199
